1. 	Introduction
1.1 	Purpose
This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document specifies the requirements for Ubwiyunge (Voice of the People), a web-based community feedback platform designed to facilitate communication between Rwandan citizens and their local government leaders. This SRS covers the complete system, including citizen issue reporting, leader response management, and community engagement features.
1.2 	Document Conventions
The following conventions are used throughout this document:
	•	Bold text indicates system components, user interface elements, or important terms 
	•	Italic text represents user roles or external systems 
	•	Code formatting denotes technical specifications, APIs, or data formats. Requirements are numbered hierarchically (e.g., REQ-1.1, REQ-1.2)
	•	Priority levels: High (Critical), Medium (Important), Low (Nice to have) 
	•	All requirements inherit the priority of their parent section unless explicitly stated otherwise

1.3 	Intended Audience and Reading Suggestions
This document is intended for: 
	•	Developers: Focus on Sections 3 (External Interface Requirements) and technical specifications 
	•	Project Managers: Read Sections 1-2 for scope and overview, Section 4 for functional requirements 
	•	Testers: Review all sections, with emphasis on functional requirements and user interface specifications 
	•	Users/Stakeholders: Focus on Sections 1-2 and user interface descriptions 
	•	System Administrators: Pay attention to the operating environment and implementation constraints 
Reading Sequence: Begin with Section 1 (Introduction) and Section 2 (Overall Description), then proceed to the sections most relevant to your role.
1.4 	Product Scope
Ubwiyunge is a web-based platform that bridges the communication gap between Rwandan citizens and their local government leaders. The software enables citizens to: 
	•	Report community issues and problems
	•	Contact appropriate local leaders directly 
	•	Track progress on submitted issues 
	•	Engage with community-wide concerns 
Business Objectives: 
	•	Improve governance transparency and accountability 
	•	Enhance citizen participation in local government 
	•	Streamline communication between citizens and leaders
	•	Create data-driven insights for better policy making 
	•	Support Rwanda's digital transformation and good governance initiatives
The platform aligns with Rwanda's Vision 2050 goals of effective governance and citizen empowerment.
2. 	Overall Description
2.1 	Product Perspective
Ubwiyunge is a new, self-contained web application designed to complement Rwanda's existing e-governance infrastructure. The system will integrate with: 
	•	Rwanda's administrative structure (Cell → Sector → District → Province) 
	•	Existing government communication channels 
	•	Mobile payment systems (future integration with MoMoPay/Airtel Money) 
	•	National ID system (future integration with Irembo services)
System Context Diagram:
[Citizens] ↔ [Web App] ↔ [Database]
     ↕           ↕
[Leaders] ↔ [Admin Panel] ↔ [File Storage]
     ↕           ↕
[SMS Gateway] ↔ [Email Service] ↔ [Notification System]

2.2 	Product Functions
The major functions of Ubwiyunge include: 
Core Functions: 
	•	Issue submission and categorization system 
	•	Leader directory and contact management 
	•	Two-way communication platform (citizens ↔ leaders) 
	•	Issue tracking and status management 
	•	Community engagement (voting, commenting, following) 
Administrative Functions: 
	•	User authentication and profile management 
	•	Leader verification and onboarding 
	•	Content moderation and system administration 
	•	Analytics and reporting dashboard 
	•	Multi-language support (Kinyarwanda/English) 
Communication Functions: 
	•	Real-time notifications 
	•	Direct messaging between citizens and leaders 
	•	Public status updates and announcements 
	•	SMS integration for feature phone users
2.3 	User Classes and Characteristics
Primary User Classes: 
Citizens (High Priority) 
	•	Frequency: Daily to weekly usage 
	•	Technical expertise: Basic to intermediate 
	•	Functions used: Issue reporting, leader contact, progress tracking 
	•	Characteristics: Rwanda residents, mobile-first users, multilingual needs 
Community Leaders (High Priority) 
	•	Frequency: Daily usage during work hours 
	•	Technical expertise: Intermediate 
	•	Functions used: Issue management, citizen communication, status updates 
	•	Characteristics: Elected/appointed officials, accountability-focused, time-constrained 
System Administrators (Medium Priority) 
	•	Frequency: Regular maintenance access 
	•	Technical expertise: Advanced 
	•	Functions used: User management, content moderation, system configuration 
	•	Characteristics: Technical staff, security-conscious Anonymous 
Visitors (Low Priority) 
	•	Frequency: Occasional browsing 
	•	Technical expertise: Basic 
	•	Functions used: Browse public issues, view leader information 
	•	Characteristics: Potential users, information seekers
2.4 	Operating Environment


Client-Side Requirements: 
	•	Web browsers: Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 14+, Edge 90+ 
	•	Mobile devices: iOS 12+, Android 8.0+ 
	•	Screen resolutions: 320px (mobile) to 1920px (desktop) 
	•	Internet connectivity: Minimum 2G, optimized for 3G/4G 
Server-Side Environment: 
	•	Operating System: Ubuntu 20.04 LTS or CentOS 8+ 
	•	Web Server: Node.js 16+ with Express framework 
	•	Database: MongoDB 5.0+ 
	•	File Storage: AWS S3 or local file system 
	•	Deployment: Docker containerization support 
Third-Party Services: 
	•	Email: SendGrid or AWS SES 
	•	SMS: Twilio or local SMS providers 
	•	Maps: Google Maps API or OpenStreetMap 
	•	Image processing: Sharp.js or similar
2.5 	Design and Implementation Constraints
Technical Constraints: 
	•	Must be responsive and mobile-first design 
	•	Maximum page load time: 3 seconds on 3G connection 
	•	Support for offline functionality (basic browsing) 
	•	Database queries must handle 10,000+ concurrent users 
	•	File uploads limited to 10MB per image 
Regulatory Constraints: 
	•	Compliance with Rwanda Data Protection Law 
	•	Government accessibility standards 
	•	Content moderation for public safety 
	•	User verification requirements for sensitive reports 
Business Constraints: 
	•	Development timeline: 6 months for MVP 
	•	Budget constraints: Open-source technologies preferred 
	•	Language requirements: Kinyarwanda and English 
	•	Integration with existing government systems preferred 
Security Constraints: 
	•	HTTPS encryption for all communications 
	•	Two-factor authentication for leader accounts 
	•	Data backup and disaster recovery procedures 
	•	Regular security audits and penetration testing
2.6 	User Documentation
The following documentation will be delivered: 
End-User Documentation: 
	•	User manual (web-based help system) 
	•	Video tutorials for key features 
	•	FAQ section with common issues 
	•	Quick start guide for new users 
	•	Mobile app usage guide 
Administrative Documentation: 
	•	System administrator manual 
	•	Leader onboarding guide 
	•	Content moderation guidelines 
	•	Troubleshooting manual 
	•	API documentation for integrations 
Delivery Formats: 
	•	Online help system integrated into the application 
	•	Downloadable PDF manuals 
	•	Video tutorials hosted on platform 
	•	Context-sensitive help tooltips
2.7 	Assumptions and Dependencies


Assumptions: 
	•	Users have basic literacy in Kinyarwanda or English 
	•	Government leaders will actively participate in the platform 
	•	Internet penetration will continue to improve in Rwanda 
	•	Citizens have access to mobile phones with cameras 
	•	Local government structure remains stable 
	•	Community leaders have email addresses and phone numbers 
Dependencies: 
	•	Reliable internet infrastructure in target deployment areas 
	•	Government approval and endorsement for leader participation 
	•	Third-party services (email, SMS, maps) remain available and affordable 
	•	MongoDB Atlas or equivalent database hosting service Cloud hosting platform (AWS, Google Cloud, or Azure) for scalability 
	•	Integration APIs from government systems (future dependency) 
	•	Community feedback and user testing during development phase 
Risk Factors: 
	•	Low initial user adoption may affect platform value 
	•	Limited leader participation could reduce effectiveness 
	•	Technical infrastructure limitations in rural areas 
	•	Potential security threats requiring ongoing mitigation 
	•	Changes in government policies affecting platform operations
3. 	External Interface Requirements
3.1 	User Interfaces
General UI Standards: 
	•	Design Philosophy: Clean, intuitive, mobile-first responsive design 
	•	Color Scheme: Rwanda national colors (blue, yellow, green) with high contrast ratios 
	•	Typography: Arial/Helvetica for English, appropriate fonts for Kinyarwanda 
	•	Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance, screen reader compatible 
	•	Language Toggle: Prominent switch between Kinyarwanda and English 
Screen Layout Standards: 
	•	Header: Logo, navigation menu, user profile, language selector 
	•	Navigation: Breadcrumb navigation, back buttons, clear menu hierarchy 
	•	Content Area: Consistent spacing, readable font sizes (minimum 16px) 
	•	Footer: Contact information, privacy policy, terms of service 
Key Interface Components: 
Dashboard Interface 
	•	Recent issues summary cards Quick action buttons (Submit Issue, Contact Leader) 
	•	Status indicators with color coding 
	•	Notification center 
Issue Submission Form 
	•	Step-by-step wizard interface 
	•	Photo upload with preview 
	•	Location selector with map integration 
	•	Category dropdown with icons 
	•	Leader suggestion panel 
Issue Detail View 
	•	Timeline of updates and responses 
	•	Photo gallery with lightbox 
	•	Leader contact card with direct action buttons 
	•	Community engagement section (votes, comments) 
Leader Directory 
	•	Search and filter interface 
	•	Contact cards with photos and information 
	•	Availability status indicators 
	•	Direct communication buttons (Call, WhatsApp, Email) 
Error Handling: 
	•	Friendly error messages in user's preferred language 
	•	Inline validation with helpful suggestions 
	•	Graceful degradation for network issues 
	•	Clear recovery instructions
3.2 	Hardware Interfaces
Mobile Device Integration: 
	•	Camera Access: Native camera integration for issue photo capture 
	•	GPS Location: Automatic location detection with user permission 
	•	Touch Interface: Optimized for touch gestures, swipe navigation 
	•	Phone Integration: Direct dialing capability for leader contacts 
	•	SMS Integration: Send/receive SMS notifications 
Desktop Hardware: 
	•	File Upload: Drag-and-drop file upload functionality 
	•	Keyboard Navigation: Full keyboard accessibility support 
	•	Print Support: Printable issue reports and leader contact lists 
	•	Multiple Monitor: Responsive layout adaptation 
Network Hardware: 
	•	Bandwidth Optimization: Progressive image loading, data compression 
	•	Offline Storage: Browser cache for offline content access 
	•	Connection Detection: Automatic retry mechanisms for poor connectivity
3.3 	Software Interfaces
Database Interface (MongoDB): 
	•	Connection: MongoDB Driver for Node.js v4.0+ 
	•	Data Models: Users, Issues, Leaders, Administrative Divisions, Responses 
	•	Queries: Aggregation pipelines for analytics, full-text search capabilities 
	•	Backup: Automated daily backups with point-in-time recovery 
Email Service Interface: 
	•	Provider: SendGrid API v3 or AWS SES 
	•	Functions: User registration emails, notification emails, password reset 
	•	Templates: HTML email templates with multilingual support 
	•	Delivery: Email delivery status tracking and bounce handling 
SMS Service Interface: 
	•	Provider: Twilio API or Rwanda Telecentre Agency SMS gateway 
	•	Functions: OTP verification, critical notifications, feature phone support 
	•	Format: SMS message templates with character limits 
	•	Delivery: Delivery confirmation and error handling 
File Storage Interface: 
	•	Service: AWS S3 or compatible object storage 
	•	File Types: JPEG, PNG, PDF documents 
	•	Processing: Image compression and thumbnail generation 
	•	Security: Signed URLs for secure access, virus scanning 
	•	Authentication Interface: JWT Tokens: JSON Web Tokens for session management 
	•	Password Hashing: bcrypt for secure password storage 
	•	Two-Factor: TOTP-based 2FA for leader accounts 
	•	OAuth Integration: Future Google/Facebook login support 
Mapping Service Interface: 
	•	Provider: Google Maps API or OpenStreetMap 
	•	Functions: Location selection, administrative boundary display 
	•	Data: Rwanda administrative divisions (Province, District, Sector, Cell) 
	•	Geocoding: Address to coordinates conversion
3.4 	Communications Interfaces   
Web Communications: 
	•	Protocol: HTTPS/TLS 1.3 for all client-server communication 
	•	API Format: RESTful JSON APIs with proper HTTP status codes 
	•	WebSocket: Real-time notifications and chat functionality 
	•	CORS: Cross-Origin Resource Sharing for API access 
	•	Rate Limiting: API throttling to prevent abuse 
Email Communications: 
	•	SMTP/API: Secure email transmission with encryption 
	•	Templates: Responsive HTML email templates 
	•	Localization: Multi-language email content 
	•	Delivery: Bounce handling and unsubscribe management 
	•	Security: SPF, DKIM, DMARC configuration 
SMS Communications: 
	•	Protocol: HTTP API calls to SMS providers 
	•	Format: UTF-8 encoded messages with Kinyarwanda support 
	•	Delivery: Status callbacks and error handling 
	•	Cost Management: Message queuing and batch processing 
	•	Security: Message encryption and secure API keys 
Push Notifications: 
	•	Web Push: Browser push notifications for real-time updates 
	•	Service Workers: Offline notification support 
	•	Personalization: User preference-based notification filtering 
	•	Delivery: Retry mechanisms for failed deliveries 
Data Transfer Specifications: 
	•	Image Upload: Maximum 10MB per file, progressive upload with resumption 
	•	API Responses: JSON format with consistent error handling 
	•	Compression: Gzip compression for all HTTP responses 
	•	Caching: HTTP cache headers for static assets 
	•	Synchronization: Conflict resolution for concurrent updates 
Security Measures: 
	•	Encryption: AES-256 for sensitive data at rest 
	•	Authentication: JWT tokens with short expiration times 
	•	Authorization: Role-based access control (RBAC) 
	•	Data Validation: Input sanitization and SQL injection prevention 
	•	Audit Trail: Comprehensive logging of all system interactions                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
