Guide to Non- Functional Requirements 
5.1 Performance Requirements
Response Time Requirements
	•	Page Load: Maximum 3 seconds on 3G networks 
	•	API Responses: Maximum 1 second for data queries 
	•	Notifications: Delivered within 5 seconds of trigger
5.2 Safety Requirements
Capacity Requirements 
	•	Concurrent Users: Support 10,000 simultaneous active users 
	•	Database: Handle 500 transactions per second during peak usage 
	•	File Uploads: Support 100 simultaneous photo uploads (10MB max each) 
Availability Requirements 
	•	System Uptime: 99.5% availability (maximum 44 hours downtime per year) 
	•	Disaster Recovery: Full system recovery within 4 hours 
	•	Data Loss: Maximum 1 hour of data loss in worst-case scenario 
Scalability Requirements 
	•	User Growth: Scale to 100,000 registered users within 2 years 
	•	Geographic: Consistent performance across all 30 districts in Rwanda 
	•	Mobile Efficiency: Maximum 2MB data consumption per user session
5.3 Security Requirements
Authentication & Access Control 
	•	Multi-Factor Authentication: Required for all leader accounts using SMS/email OTP 
	•	Password Policy: Minimum 8 characters with complexity requirements 
	•	Role-Based Access: Citizens, Leaders, and Administrators with distinct permissions 
	•	Session Security: Auto-logout after 30 minutes; account lockout after 5 failed attempts 
Data Protection 
	•	Encryption: HTTPS/TLS 1.3 for data in transit; AES-256 for data at rest 
	•	Privacy Controls: Anonymous issue reporting option; user data export capabilities 
	•	File Security: Encrypted photo storage with secure access controls 
Compliance & Legal 
	•	Rwanda Data Protection Law: Full compliance with national regulations 
	•	Government Standards: Adherence to Rwanda's e-Government security framework 
	•	Content Security: Input validation to prevent attacks; content moderation systems 
System Security 
	•	Infrastructure: Regular security updates, firewall protection, DDoS mitigation 
	•	Monitoring: 24/7 security monitoring with incident response procedures 
	•	Backups: Encrypted automated backups with secure offsite storage 
Operational Security 
	•	Administrative Controls: Multi-person authorization for critical system changes 
	•	Audit Trails: Complete logging of all user and administrative actions 
	•	User Education: In-app security guidance and phishing protection warnings
5.4 Software Quality Attributes
Reliability & Availability 
	•	Availability: 99.5% uptime with maximum 4-hour recovery time from failures 
	•	Reliability: Zero data loss during normal operations; maximum 1-hour data loss in disaster scenarios
	•	Robustness: System continues operating with degraded performance during network issues or high load
Usability & Accessibility 
	•	Usability: New users can submit their first issue within 3 minutes without training 
	•	Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance for users with disabilities 
	•	Ease of Use: Prioritized over advanced features - simple, intuitive interface for all literacy levels
	•	Mobile-First: Touch-optimized interface with large buttons and clear navigation 
Performance & Scalability 
	•	Scalability: Horizontal scaling to support 10x user growth without architectural changes 
	•	Performance: Consistent response times across all Rwanda's network conditions (2G to 4G) 
	•	Efficiency: Minimal data usage (≤2MB per session) to ensure affordability
Maintainability & Flexibility 
	•	Maintainability: Modular architecture allowing feature updates without system downtime 
	•	Adaptability: Easy configuration for different administrative levels or neighboring countries 
	•	Testability: 80%+ automated test coverage with continuous integration 
	•	Interoperability: REST APIs for integration with existing government systems 
Portability & Compatibility 
	•	Cross-Platform: Works on all devices (desktop, mobile, tablets) and major browsers 
	•	Technology Independence: Database-agnostic design for easy migration between platforms 
	•	Language Flexibility: Easy addition of new languages beyond Kinyarwanda and English 
Security & Data Quality 
	•	Data Integrity: 99.9% accuracy in data storage and retrieval operations 
	•	Security: Multi-layered protection with regular security audits 
	•	Correctness: Input validation ensures data quality and prevents system errors

6.SDLC MODEL
Choice of Development Methodology 
Agile Development with Scrum Framework 
	•	Enables continuous stakeholder feedback from citizens and leaders 
	•	Accommodates changing governance requirements during development 
	•	Reduces project risks through iterative delivery and early testing 
Development Phases and Milestones 
Phase 1: Foundation - User authentication, basic UI, and database setup complete Phase 2: Core Features - Issue management, leader directory, and response system operational Phase 3: Enhanced Features - Community engagement, multi-language support, and analytics implemented Phase 4: Deployment - Complete testing, security audit, and production-ready system delivered (weeks beyond week 12) 
Testing Strategies 
	•	Unit Testing: 80% code coverage with automated tests 
	•	Integration Testing: API and database validation each sprint 
	•	User Acceptance Testing: Stakeholder testing after each phase 
	•	Performance Testing: Load testing for 10,000 concurrent users 
	•	Security Testing: Vulnerability assessments and penetration testing 
Deployment Approach 
Blue-Green Deployment using: 
	•	Docker for containerization 
	•	Kubernetes for orchestration and scaling 
	•	AWS/Azure cloud infrastructure 
	•	GitHub Actions for CI/CD pipeline 
	•	MongoDB Atlas for database hosting 
	•	Cloudflare for CDN and security 
Maintenance and Support Model 
	•	Level 1 Support: User issues (4-hour response) 
	•	Level 2 Support: Technical issues (2-hour response) 
	•	Level 3 Support: Critical bugs (1-hour response)



